Use this prompt in another chat:

> **Prompt:**
>
> Remove **only the unnecessary empty blank lines** from the following code.
>
> **Rules:**
>
> * Do **not** change any code, formatting, indentation, spacing, variable names, function names, JSX, HTML, classes, `div`s, or logic.
> * Do **not** refactor or optimize anything.
> * Do **not** add or remove any code.
> * Preserve the existing formatting exactly as it is.
> * **Only** delete consecutive empty lines so there is at most **one** blank line between code blocks where appropriate.
> * Return the **entire file** with the empty lines removed.
> * Do **not** wrap the output in Markdown or explain the changes—just return the cleaned code.
>
> Example:
>
> Before:
>
> ```jsx
> <div>
>
>
> <h1>Hello</h1>
>
>
> <p>World</p>
> </div>
> ```
>
> After:
>
> ```jsx
> <div>
> <h1>Hello</h1>
> <p>World</p>
> </div>
> ```
>
> Here is the code:
>
> ```jsx
> // Paste your code here
> ```

This prompt will instruct the model to remove only blank lines while leaving everything else untouched.
